<p><u><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS"><font size=3D"+3">Looking at the Degree =
of
the Vertex and Graph</font></font></u>
<br><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS">&nbsp;</font>
<br><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS">&nbsp;</font>
<br><u><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS"><font size=3D"+2">Degree of Verticies</=
font></font></u>
<br><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS">&nbsp;</font>
<br><font face=3D"Comic Sans MS"><font size=3D"+2">To analize a graph it is=
 important
to look at the <a href=3D"http://www.geom.uiuc.edu/~doty/glossary.html#Degr=
ee%20of%20a%20vertex">degree of a vertex</a>.&nbsp;
One way to find the degree is to count the number of edges which has that
vertx as an endpoint.&nbsp; An easy way to do this is to draw a circle
around the vertex and count the number of edges that cross the circle.</fon=
t></font>
<br>&nbsp;
<br>&nbsp;

</p><p><img src=3D"http://www.geom.uiuc.edu/~doty/degree.gif" border=3D"0" =
height=3D"298" width=3D"303" align=3D"LEFT">
